brewery.brewery_description:
Copperhead Restaurant Brewery in Cooroy is part of the new wave of Brew Pubs - a brewery with a real focus on quality food & beer made for consumption on premise only. 
​
Enjoy a burger at the bar with a cold beer or sit down to an a la carte meal with full restaurant service at pub prices. Extensive wine list and full stocked bar is also available, making Copperhead a great choice for your next function, wedding or big night out.

We are a small batch bespoke brewery, with an ever changing stable of beers. We do not wholesale our beers to anyone, you can only get them here. We aim to have a regular 7 very sessionable beers on tap, with the addition of 'EB's' (experimental batches) to change with the seasons. These 'EB's' will be for the craft beer aficionado. Being an independent small batch brewery, it gives us the freedom to make our beer without fining agents or preservatives making our beer is 100% pure & unfiltered.

items.badge_description: Want to enjoy a day of brews, but need to keep your wits sharp? There are plenty of delicious brews under 5% for you to sip on throughout the day. That's 475 different beers with an ABV of 5% and lower.

At a new place and don't want to choose a pint of something you may not like? Grab a few tasters! Enjoy some small pours and then decide which to upgrade to a full pour. That's 165 checkins with the serving style of Taster. Try 5 more for Level 34! Want to learn more about this badge? Check out our podcast

items.badge_description: Celebrate women and non-binary individuals in craft beer! Every year the Pink Boots Society (PBS) hosts Collaboration Brew Day where teams come together to brew a collab beer that supports the PBS mission to support, inspire, and encourage the professional development of women and non-binary people in the industry.
